The ideal length for a password is at least 12 characters, but ideally 16-20 characters. It's important to use a mix of uppercase and lowercase letters, numbers, and special characters to make the password as strong as possible. One way to create strong, memorable passwords is to use a passphrase instead of a single word. For example, instead of using "password123", you could use "CorrectHorseBatteryStaple". This is a phrase that is easy to remember, but difficult to guess. Another tip is to use a password generator to create strong, unique passwords for each of your accounts.
